# UI product sync

Apply when editing front-end UI, design docs, or Tailwind/theme tokens.

---

## Before any UI work

Read in order:

1. [PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md](../../claude-design-docs/PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md)
2. [PRODUCT-VISION.md](../../claude-design-docs/PRODUCT-VISION.md)
3. [UI-PRINCIPLES.md](../../claude-design-docs/UI-PRINCIPLES.md)
4. [SCREEN-INTENT-MAP.md](../../claude-design-docs/SCREEN-INTENT-MAP.md)
5. Target screen in [`claude-design-docs/prototype/Career OS.html`](../../claude-design-docs/prototype/Career%20OS.html)
6. [docs/CHECKPOINT.md](../../docs/CHECKPOINT.md) — P0 scope + demo script

Compare three views:

- **Prototype intent** — layout, copy, wow moments
- **Implemented UI** — `apps/web/` when present
- **Product goals** — CHECKPOINT wow features

Resolve conflicts using the hierarchy in PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH (goals → screen intent → prototype → code).

---

## After UI sessions — update canonical docs

If the session changed **UI paradigm**, update docs in the **same session** (before ending):

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New/changed route or flow | [SCREEN-INTENT-MAP.md](../../claude-design-docs/SCREEN-INTENT-MAP.md) |
| Token / color / typography | [design-tokens.md](../../claude-design-docs/design-tokens.md) |
| Deliberate prototype divergence | [PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md](../../claude-design-docs/PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md) → Implementation notes |
| New shared component pattern | PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH Implementation notes + UI-PRINCIPLES component table |

**UI paradigm change** means any of:

- New reusable component pattern
- Layout shift (split ratios, hero placement)
- Design token change
- New screen or altered navigation flow
- Status UX or graph interaction change

Skill for explicit sync: [.cursor/skills/ui-product-sync/SKILL.md](../skills/ui-product-sync/SKILL.md)

---

## Do not

- Ship UI that weakens P0 wow (Forge stream, validation, adaptive graph) without CHECKPOINT update
- Introduce gamification / LMS patterns rejected in UI-PRINCIPLES
- Rename skill status enums without API + CHECKPOINT alignment

